                                Hydrography is the science of studying and collecting the scientific characteristics and natural phenomena of water bodies such as seas, oceans, rivers and lakes, and the representation and use of their data and information to provide maximum degree of navigational safety. It is an applied science in common with other sciences such as topography, navigation, geodesy, geology and nature. In addition to providing and ensuring navigational safety, hydrography has many uses that support economic and defence aspects, scientific research, maritime security and service of sectors related to maritime affairs.
                            </p>




